# YouTube Organic MCP Server — Environment Variables
#
# Auth uses Google OAuth 2.0: a long-lived refresh token plus your OAuth client
# (client_id + client_secret). The server mints short-lived access tokens on
# demand, so nothing expires day-to-day.
#
# Setup:
#   1. In Google Cloud Console (any project), enable:
#        - YouTube Data API v3
#        - YouTube Analytics API
#   2. Use an OAuth client (Desktop type) — you can reuse the one your other
#      Google MCPs already use.
#   3. Run scripts/get_youtube_token.py to complete the OAuth flow and get a
#      refresh token (authorize with the account that owns the channel).
#
# Required scopes: youtube.readonly, yt-analytics.readonly

# ── Single-account mode ────────────────────────────────────────────
YOUTUBE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com
YOUTUBE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
YOUTUBE_REFRESH_TOKEN=your_refresh_token

# ── Multi-account mode (overrides the three vars above) ─────────────
# YOUTUBE_ACCOUNTS=[{"name":"myfunnycaptions","client_id":"...","client_secret":"...","refresh_token":"1//..."}]
